commText: Jaiswal and Kohler-Cadmore are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Swapnil Singh will open the attack
Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, no run, almost an outswinger from round the wicket, drifts away late across off, and Jaiswal knocks it to mid-off
Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, no run, another outswinger, goes away off a length, and Jaiswal blocks
Jaiswal gets into position for a reverse-hit, and having seen that, Swapnil decides to pull out
Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, 1 run, length ball drifting across off, Jaiswal gets a thick leading edge wide of short third

Swapnil Singh to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, flat length ball on off at 93kph, hint of turn, and Kohler-Cadmore punches it from the crease to the right of short cover. Faf throws himself across to cut it off
Swapnil Singh to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, full ball drifting in on the pads, Kohler-Cadmore whips it to deep midwicket
Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, no run, fuller than a length on off, swinging away from Jaiswal and he mistimes the drive to mid-off. Tight first over from Swapnil Singh
Mohammed Siraj, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, pitched up just outside off, hint of outswing, and Kohler-Cadmore punches into the off-side ring
Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, full and wide outside off, Kohler-Cadmore goes for a big drive but the ball swings away and takes a thick edge to deep third
Siraj to Jaiswal, 1 run, close to the blockhole outside off, Jaiswal looks to drive and toe-ends it to the left of mid-off
Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, 137.4kph length ball on middle and leg, Kohler-Cadmore hangs back and tucks it to mid-on. Slight mix-up between the two batters but Jaiswal turns back in time

Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, leg byes, 1 run, 140.7kph full ball slanted in, Kohler-Cadmore looks to hit across the line but is late on it. Gets hit on the pad and picks up a leg bye. That was going well down the leg-side, hence no appeal
Swapnil Singh bowling the first over in IPL 2024 Overs: 5 Runs conceded: 32 Wickets: 3 (David Warner, Prabhsimran Singh, Wriddhiman Saha) ER: 6.4 Dots: 16
Siraj to Jaiswal, 1 run, full outside off, Jaiswal looks to break the shackles and throws his bat at it. It goes in the air off a thick edge and falls wide of deep third
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, no run, length ball outside off, hint of inswing, and Jaiswal drives on the up to backward point. He timed it well but couldn't find the gap
Backward point is pushed back to the boundary

Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, FOUR, difficult chance goes down at slip! Green is much wider than a conventional first slip, and can only get one hand to this as he stretches across. Full outside off, Jaiswal looks to loft it down the ground but it swings away and goes flying off the edge. Went quickly to the right of Green who only gets fingertips and can't hang on
Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, FOUR, short of length outside off, enough width for Jaiswal to free the arms and he slaps it hard. Gets it to the right of deep backward point for four
Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, no run, beaten outside off this time as he throws his hands at this outswinger
Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, FOUR, too full from Dayal and it's crunched through the off-side. Line is outside off, Jaiswal goes hard on the drive and nails it through the covers

Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, FOUR, Dayal kicks the turf in frustration as Jaiswal gets another boundary to finish the over. Back of a length outside off, he chops it off a thick under-edge wide of slip where Green gets a hand but fails to cut it off. After two tight overs to start, the pressure is released as RR pick up four boundaries off the third
Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, FOUR, oh lovely timing. Length ball on middle and leg, Kohler-Cadmore hangs back and whips it beautifully through midwicket. Diving effort from Faf in vain
Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, FOUR, that's a hit-me delivery! Wide half-volley outside off, Kohler-Cadmore goes after it and spanks it through cover. Suddenly the boundaries are flowing for RR
Siraj to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, back of a length at the body, Kohler-Cadmore looks to pull but gets a thick under-edge behind square
Siraj to Jaiswal, no run, length ball on off, defended

Siraj to Jaiswal, FOUR, misfield and four! Short at the body, Jaiswal pulls it behind square and Swapnil is a lot wider than a conventional fine leg. Still, he should've cut it off with his sliding effort as he got to the ball comfortably. But it sneaks through to the boundary
Siraj to Jaiswal, no run, full ball on middle and leg, Jaiswal pushes it to the left of Siraj who gets a hand as he goes down in followthrough

Yash Dayal to Kohler-Cadmore, 1 run, Maxwell drops a simple chance in the deep! Back of a length around the waist, Kohler-Cadmore pulls it in the air and it should be a sitter for him at deep square leg. He goes with the reverse-cup but it pops out
Yash Dayal to Jaiswal, 1 run, slower dipping full toss on the pads, Jaiswal flicks to deep midwicket
Yash Dayal to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, slower ball floated up on the pads, Kohler-Cadmore flicks to midwicket

Yash Dayal to Kohler-Cadmore, FOUR, pulled in the air again, but gets it well in front of square this time! 138.6kph back of a length delivery around the waist, Kohler-Cadmore hangs back and pulls it over midwicket
Yash Dayal to Kohler-Cadmore, no run, slower yorker on leg stump, Kohler-Cadmore backs away to drive through the off-side and squeezes it to cover
Yash Dayal to Kohler-Cadmore, FOUR, firmly punched off the back foot, and finds the gap! Back of a length on off, slower one, and Kohler-Cadmore times it beautifully through extra cover
Lockie Ferguson, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Ferguson to Jaiswal, no run, Jaiswal screams in frustration as he fails to capitalise on a full toss. It's a slower one on the pads, he flicks it well but finds midwicket
Ferguson to Jaiswal, 1 run, back of a length on off, gently punched wide of point
Ferguson to Kohler-Cadmore, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Ferguson to Kohler-Cadmore, out Bowled!! Ferguson roars in delight as he provides the breakthrough. RCB needed that desperately as the opening pair was starting to flourish. This is a brilliantly executed slower yorker. It dips late, sneaks under the attempted drive from Kohler-Cadmore and knocks over off stump. Dayal bowled a couple of these deliveries in his previous over as well, and now Ferguson uses it to good effect. Kohler-Cadmore b Ferguson 20(15) [4s-4]
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Ferguson to Samson, no run, good length on off, defended forward
Ferguson to Samson, 1 run, slower length ball on middle and leg, Samson tucks it to deep midwicket
Ferguson to Jaiswal, no run, good length on middle, slower one again, and Jaiswal drives it back to Ferguson

Summary (Overs 1-6) -- 47/1, 7.83 rpo -- Swapnil bowls a brilliant tight over -- Siraj backs up with a quiet over -- Green drops Jaiswal on 3 - a tough chance off Dayal (2.2) -- Jaiswal takes Dayal for 4 fours in the same over -- RR gain speed as Siraj leaks 13 in his second over -- Maxwell drops TKC on 11, over costs 10 (4.1) -- Ferguson knocks over TKC and kills momentum (5.3)
Swapnil Singh [1.0-0-2-0] is back into the attack

Swapnil Singh to Samson, SIX, short, with the arm and gets some extra bounce. Samson rocks back and rides the bounce nicely to pull it over a flailing deep mid-wicket fielder. Greets a returning Swapnil Singh with a six
Swapnil Singh to Samson, 1 run, pushed a bit quicker and on a length, punched to the left of mid-wicket for a single
Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, 1 run, fired onto the pads, driven towards long-on by Jaiswal
Swapnil Singh to Samson, 1 run, pitched up and spinning away from off, push driven to long-off

Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, FOUR, fired wide outside off, Jaiswal accepts the width gleefully and flat bats the drive through extra cover for a boundary. Always running away from the fielder in the deep

Swapnil Singh to Jaiswal, FOUR, 96.1 clicks, a short and wide delivery from Swapnil. Jaiswal gets closer and cuts it powerfully through backward point for a boundary. Fielder dived over the ball and there was enough power on the shot to evade the man in the deep
Ferguson to Samson, 1 run, 143.8 clicks, length ball angling onto off, Samson runs it down to third-man

Ferguson to Jaiswal, FOUR, edged and away!! A quick, full one that was angling across. Jaiswal goes for a big slash and gets an edge that runs away to the left of DK. No slip and third-man is too wide
Ferguson to Jaiswal, 1 run, 145.2 clicks, length ball angling onto off stump, dabbed towards square third-man
Ferguson to Samson, 1 run, pace off and onto middle and leg, Samson closes the bat face towards deep backward square leg
Tom Kohler Cadmore vs Lockie Ferguson in T20s \nThree balls, three dismissals

Ferguson to Jaiswal, 2 runs, back of length and on off stump, cut square of the wicket slightly to the right of the fielder. Jaiswal takes a chance on Kohli's arm and is quick enough to reach back just in time despite a pretty flat throw from the deep
Ferguson to Jaiswal, 1 run, low full toss, Jaiswal shuffles in and clips it towards deep mid-wicket

Time-out. Rajasthan looking good in the chase and RCB's sloopy fielding hasn't helped either. Jaiswal looks set and Samson has the steely determination of a captain in his eyes today. The dew is also helping the chasing side. RCB need wickets and need them quickly to sneak back in this game.
Karn Sharma, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Karn Sharma to Jaiswal, 1 run, tossed up delivery at the stumps, driven to the left of Kohli at long-on. Jaiswal wanted a second but sent back by his skipper

Karn Sharma to Samson, 1 run, tossed up and wide, driven powerfully to the right of sweeper cover. Good pick-up and throw from Swapnil Singh, restricts it to just a single. Samson wanted a second and was sent back. He was pretty casual coming back and had a look back towards Jaiswal before even grounding his bat. The ball was in Karn Sharma's hand then. A chance of a run out missed. Just needed a bit more presence of mind from the bowler.
Karn Sharma to Jaiswal, 1 run, flat and on the pads, clipped towards mid-wicket
Karn Sharma to Samson, 1 run, on a length and straight, punched to the right of the bowler
Karn Sharma to Jaiswal, 1 run, fuller on middle and leg, Jaiswal strides forward to drive down to long-on
Karn Sharma to Samson, 1 run, flat delivery onto middle stump, Samson backs away slightly and punches it down to long-off

Jaiswal was down on his haunches last over after denying the second run off the 2nd ball. Seems like a bit of heat exhaustion, he seems a bit devoid of energy. Something to keep an eye on for the rest of the innings
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Green to Samson, 1 run, hard length delivery onto the thigh pad, slapped towards deep square

Review taken for a caught behind. DK and Cam Green are super confident. Jaiswal has a sheepish look on his face, the look of a man who knows he might have edged that. Yes, the ball rolls off his gloves towards the keeper. Jaiswal is out
Green to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Green to Jaiswal, out Caught by Karthik!! A clutch breakthrough from Cameron Green, not for the first time this season!! A length ball onto middle stump, Jaiswal shuffles away to try and ramp it over 45. Misses his shot and the ball grazes his glove on the way to the keeper. A famished looking Yashasvi Jaiswal walks back, slams his bat onto the ground in frustration before reaching the dugout. Jaiswal c Karthik b Green 45(30) [4s-8]
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Green to Riyan Parag, 1 run, full onto the pads, clipped towards deep square to get going
Green to Samson, 1 run, pitched up on middle and leg, pushed out to long-on
Green to Riyan Parag, 1 run, short near the shoulder, pulled into the ground towards square leg for a quick run
Green to Samson, 1 run, back of length angling onto the hips, tucked towards mid-wicket. Good over from Cam Green, five runs and a wicket.
Karn Sharma to Samson, THATS OUT!! Stumped!!

Karn Sharma to Samson, wide, out Stumped!! Gone! A rush of blood, akin to the Samson of old ends his innings. Dances down the track and shows his cards too soon. Karn Sharma reads the hand and floats one wide outside off, gets it to spin away further. Beyond the reach of Samson who is made to look silly in the middle of the wicket. Easy stumping for Karthik. RCB fighting back in the contest. Samson is fuming, throws his bat down in frustration and yelps out as he walks back to the pavillion. Samson st Karthik b Karn Sharma 17(13) [6s-1]
Sanju Samson vs spin in 2024 Runs: 179 Balls: 128 Dismissals: 1 (today) SR: 139.84
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Karn Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, that's some way to announce yourself in an eliminator. A flat delivery onto middle and leg, keeps a tad low. Jurel stays back and slaps the pull to the left of deep mid-wicket. Off the mark with a boundary
Karn Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, pushed through onto the pads, clipped to deep square
Karn Sharma to Riyan Parag, FOUR, cheeky but cute from Riyan Parag. Shuffles in slightly and gets just a bit of bat on the sweep to guide it very fine for a boundary
Karn Sharma to Riyan Parag, no run, pushed fuller and closer to off, defended by Parag
Karn Sharma to Riyan Parag, wide, wide outside off, spins away further. Parag shoulders arms and the umpire calls it
Karn Sharma to Riyan Parag, 1 run, pushed fuller onto off, driven to the left of Karn for a single
Karn Sharma to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, floated too full on off, driven down to long-off
Green to Dhruv Jurel, no run, banged in short on the body, Jurel ducks under it
Green to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, angling onto the pads on a length, clipped towards deep square. An electric pickup and throw by Kohli from the deep. Parag smartly decides against the second very early
Green to Riyan Parag, no run, yorker length on off, stabbed back to Green who gets his right hand to it to stop
Review taken by RCB for a caught behind. Everyone is asking each other if they heard something, nobody seems convinced totally but DK takes the chance. Nope, no bat on that one. Review lost
Green to Riyan Parag, no run, superb bouncer from Cameron Green. Goes over the bat and just over the helmet as Parag tried to pull it away.
Green to Riyan Parag, 1 run, cutter outside off, on a length. Run down towards third-man
Green to Dhruv Jurel, no run, good length and straight, defended to the right of Cameron Green. Just two runs off the over, Cam Green is quietly bowling a match altering spell here in Ahmedabad. I0$
Lockie Ferguson [2.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack
Ferguson to Riyan Parag, 3 runs, very full onto off stump, Parag digs it out to the left of the cover fielder on the drive. Doesn't have the timing to go to the fence, cut off by deep point
Ferguson to Dhruv Jurel, no run, full and angling onto middle and leg, defended to mid-wicket
Ferguson to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, back of length and wide, Jurel gets an outside edge on the slash towards third-man

Ferguson to Riyan Parag, SIX, powerful!! A pace off back of length delivery outside off. Riyan Parag seemed ready for that one and used all his might on the pull shot. Slams it across the line, in front of square beyond deep mid-wicket for a maximum
Ferguson to Riyan Parag, no run, good length and skids on quickly with a bit of angle back in. Inside edge onto the pad flap
Ferguson to Riyan Parag, 1 run, fuller delivery onto off, punched confidently towards sweeper cover

Summary (Overs 7-13) -- 64/2, 9.14 rpo -- Lockie goes for 10 runs in his 2nd over -- Karn not alert to a runout when Sanju didn't ground his bat (8.2) -- Tiring Jaiswal gloves Green to DK (9.2) -- Sanju steps out too early and Karn smartly has him stumped (10.1) -- But Karn goes for 12 runs in the same over -- Green delivers another tight over, RCB lose a review -- Parag smacks Ferguson for a six
Green to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Green to Riyan Parag, out Dhruv Jurel Run Out!! 1 run completed Jeez! I0$ A sublime effort from the former RCB skipper gets a wicket out of nowhere for his side. A back of length delivery, pulled powerfully to the left of Kohli at deep square. He charges onto the ball and throws it flat right onto the bowler's receiving arms at the non striker's end. Jurel was a bit casual while running the second, and ends up costing him his wicket. Never mess with Virat Kohli's arm! Shashank Singh and PBKS learnt it the hard way. That cost them a game in Dharamsala, will the same happen to RR today? Dhruv Jurel run out (Kohli/Green) 8(8) [4s-1]
Hetmyer comes on as Impact Sub. Yuzi Chahal goes out
Shimron Hetmyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Green to Riyan Parag, no run, 138.6 clicks, back of length and generates steep bounce onto middle and leg. Defended to the right of Green
Green to Riyan Parag, 1 run, back of length and straight, punched off the splice to the right of the bowler for a single
Green to Hetmyer, no run, good length stump lined delivery on off, punched into the ground towards point
Green to Hetmyer, 1 run, good length and straight, punched down the ground for a single
Green to Riyan Parag, 1 run, fuller delivery on off, turned towards long-on for a single. Another tight over from Cam Green, required rate nearing 10 now.

Time-out. RCB have clawed their way back into the game purely off the back of a dreamy Cam Green spell and some electric fielding from Virat Kohli. Rajasthan were in control of this chase but three quick wickets have let the cat amongst the pigeons now. A big game for Riyan Parag. He's had a coming of age season, but can he get his side through in a knockout game? He dreams of being that guy for RR and maybe for India in the future, can he be that guy today with his idol Virat Kohli in the rival camp?
Mohammed Siraj [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Siraj to Riyan Parag, 1 run, good length on off stump, punched down to long-off
Siraj to Hetmyer, 1 run, slower bouncer, Hetmyer top edges the pull towards deep backward square leg after a few bounces

Siraj to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, pitched fuller onto leg, clipped to the right of long-on. Parag was content with a single when there was always a second on offer. Hetmyer is almost at the non striker's end when Parag starts running. A better throw and he was in trouble. Seems to be a bit rattled with the Jurel run out last over.
Siraj to Riyan Parag, 1 run, length ball on off, Parag inside halves the pull towards deep mid-wicket
Siraj to Hetmyer, FOUR, 139.8 clicks, banged in short on the body, Hetmyer goes for the pull shot and gets a top edge on it. Flies away towards the fine leg boundary. I0$
Siraj to Hetmyer, wide, short ball angling across, a bit too wide and Hetmyer lets it pass. Called wide on height
Siraj to Hetmyer, 1 run, good length onto the thigh pad, tucked towards deep backward square leg. 11 off the over, quells the asking rate slightly.

Green to Hetmyer, SIX, jeez, that seemed like a mishit but it goes all the way. The muscles of these Caribbean lads are unreal. A short ball, was pace off and Hetmyer goes for a big heave across the line. Off the toe-end but flies over wide long-on for a maximum
Green to Hetmyer, 1 run, pushed fuller at the stumps, slammed down to long-on

Green to Riyan Parag, SIX, what a shot!! A muscular inside out drive over extra cover that sails all the way for six. Fuller length on off stump, Parag backs away and smokes it over deep extra cover. Hits it as clean as a whistle. 'What a talent this boy is', quips Gavaskar on air and we couldn't agree more!!

Green to Riyan Parag, FOUR, banged in short onto middle, Parag arches his back and backs away to run it down towards the third-man boundary. A clever stroke with the fielder inside the circle, just had to get his connection fine enough. I0$
Green to Riyan Parag, no run, back of length on off, Parag defends it dead off the backfoot
Green to Riyan Parag, no run, back of length at the stumps, pulled towards mid-wicket
Yash Dayal [2.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack
Yash Dayal to Hetmyer, 1 run, slower bouncer outside off. Hetmyer with a big heave across the line. On the bounce to deep mid-wicket
Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, 1 run, tried the dipping slower yorker, ends as a low full toss. Parag swings it away towards deep mid-wicket

Yash Dayal to Hetmyer, FOUR, not a soul moved as Hetmyer played that shot. Just a few purple jerseys in the crowd lifted themselves off their seats. Another attempted yorker, ends as a low full toss and Hetmyer drills it down the ground to the right of Dayal
Yash Dayal to Hetmyer, FOUR, good length and wide outside off, Hetmyer slashes it over backward point for a boundary. I0$
Yash Dayal to Hetmyer, 1 run, slower, full delivery. Clipped towards deep mid-wicket
Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, no run, slower delivery outside off, a big swing and a miss for Parag. 39 runs off the last 3 overs, RR have totally tilted the tide once again.
Mohammed Siraj [3.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Siraj to Hetmyer, 1 run, full on the boots, flicked towards deep backward square leg
Siraj to Riyan Parag, wide, attempted yorker, slides down the leg side
Siraj to Riyan Parag, wide, slower bouncer from Siraj, goes over the head of Parag who was arching down low slightly. The bowler isn't happen with that decision and RCB review. Another review lost.
Siraj to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Siraj to Riyan Parag, out Bowled!! Knocked over!! Pitched up delivery and it goes through Riyan Parag. The batter goes for a big heave across the line. Misses and his stumps are a mess. Siraj does a forlorn looking 'Siu' celebration. He knows that the wicket has perhaps come a bit too late. Riyan Parag b Siraj 36(26) [4s-2 6s-2]
Rovman Powell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Siraj to Powell, 1 run, full delivery on the pads, glanced towads deep backward square leg
Siraj to Hetmyer, 1 run, low full toss, slammed to the right of Maxwell at deep mid-wicket. Just a single
Siraj to Powell, 1 run, very full at the stumps, pushed out to long-on
Siraj to Hetmyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Hetmyer, out Caught by du Plessis!! there's still some life in this contest! A full delivery angling across to middle and leg, Hetmyer goes for a big flick and gets a leading edge. Flies up and Faf from covers runs back. Almost overruns it and adjust well as the ball is coming down to cling on for a superb catch. A magical Faf catch turned the tide against CSK in their previous game, will lighting strike twice? Siraj makes a 'calm down' gesture towards someone in the dressing room, this game is anything but calm now!! Hetmyer c du Plessis b Siraj 26(14) [4s-3 6s-1]
Ravichandran Ashwin, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Lockie Ferguson [3.0-0-23-1] is back into the attack

Ferguson to Powell, FOUR, how clever was that!! For his brute force, Rovman Powell can also be a man with panache. A quick, full and wide delivery. Powell plays it late and guides his drive square between backward point and short third

Ferguson to Powell, FOUR, edged and sneaks through!! A full, quick delivery angling onto off stump. Catches an edge as Powell tried to defend. Scraps to the right of short third for consecutive boundaries
Ferguson to Powell, no run, good length on off, punched towards backward point
Ferguson to Powell, no run, 140.8 clicks, good length and straight. Defended to the right of Ferguson and he makes a diving stop to deny RR a single
Ferguson to Powell, no run, slower delivery onto off, defended back to Ferguson. Three dot balls now after two boundaries!

Ferguson to Powell, SIX, Powell pumps his fists in delight as RR survive a mini scare to get through the game! A slower full delivery at the stumps. Powell read it off the hand, waited and then chipped it straight down the ground. A flat six that lands just over the ropes. Game taken care off with an over to spare. RR win by 4 wickets, RCB eliminated.

23:25 Local Time, 17:55 GMT, 23:25 IST: I0$ The murmured chants of 'Ee Sala Cup Namde' drown out into the neighboring Sabarmati river as RCB fans are forced to lick their wounds once again. Just like their season, this game saw them resurrect from the dead on mutliple occasions, but ultimately their sloopy fielding early on came to cost them. Chasing a slightly sub par total of 173, Rajasthan got a decent start with Kohler-Cadmore and Jaiswal both getting runs. Despite the Englishman's wicket, Samson and Jaiswal stitched on a partnership and at a point RR were cantering to a win. However, an inspired spell from Cam Green, coupled with a needless Samson stumping and an electric run out from Virat Kohli made the game interesting. Rajasthan needed 58 off the final six, but Riyan Parag held his own to augment what has been a breakthrough season for him. He took down Green for a six and a four, as Hetmyer played the perfect supporting role from the other end. Both batters couldn't stay the course, but the equation was down to a run a ball, before Rovman Powell added the finishing touches. Stick on for the presentations...

Faf du Plessis: With the dew coming, we felt we were short with the bat. Did think we were 20 runs shy of what was a good score. Credit to the boys - they fought really well. That's all you can ask for. If you look at naturally assessing the pitch and conditions, you would say it's a 180 pitch because it was swinging upfront and was quite slow. But what we've found out this season, with the impact player, the par score isn't enough any more. Also with the dew coming in. Extremely proud. Lot of teams - their wheels would've fallen off after 1 from 9. To come back like that, six games in a row, takes a lot of heart and character. We weren't special tonight in terms of pushing that extra 20 runs with the bat.

Powell: It (situation) wasn't that difficult. It was situation where you had to put bat to ball, thankfully i minimized the pressure. I wanted to tell him to be positive than look for singles and unfortunately he got out. (On his batting position) If it was up to me I would take it a little bit earlier. Having said that we have quality batters and you have to accept the role and I am looking forward to contribute more in this role. sometimes you need things like these (Four catches). First catch (off Faf) was the one that let me take four catches. If I had put that down, it would be a haan, tough day in the field kind of situation. When you have good player like Faf and Virat you want those half chances to come to you. You put the body on the line. We have been playing good cricket overall this season, last few games we messed up. Guys are looking forward to playing in Chennai.

Stats by Roshan Gede

Sanju Samson: What cricket and life has taught us is we will have some good and some really bad phases. But we need to have the character to bounce back. Really happy with the way we fielded, batted and bowled today. Credit to the bowlers, they are always looking at what the opposition batters would do and what fields to set. Credit goes to Sanga and bowling coach Shane Bond as well. They've spent a lot of time in hotel rooms discussing these things. Plus Ashwin and Boult are experienced lads. (On Parag and Jaiswal) They are 22 each, so is Jurel. With very little experience, the way they are performing at this level is amazing. (On his health) I'm not a 100% actually. There is a bug in the dressing room, lots of coughs and a lot of people are a bit unwell. (Going forward) Rovman finished that off well. I think we have a travel day and rest now, looking forward to the next game.

R Ashwin | Player of the Match: We haven't done very well in the last few games. We didn't put par scores and we lost Buttler, and Hetmyer was injured. Today's win was important. We were a bit rusty chasing it, but this win will give us some confidence. In the first half, I felt my body wasn't moving too well for the first half of the season. I had an abdomen injury as well. I am aging as well. To come into the tournament from Test cricket was difficult, I needed some time to get that bowling rhytmn. But once you have committed to your franchise, you want to go through with the season. I think we hit the right lengths, the way Boult was bowling, he got a bit of swing and seam movement. In the second innings, I don't think there was a lot of dew. I think there were some exceptional shots from our boys to get that chase. I think our greatest strength is the exuberance of youth and the experience we have got to support that. Now that Hettie is back in, and Rovman got a few boundaries today as well. We've got Keshav sitting outside. We have the right momentum for this team going forward.

So the RCB juggernaut has been quashed by the collective might of Rajasthan. The Royals shook off the cobwebs of four straight defeats as the team stepped up for this eliminator. Despite all his runs and electric fielding, Virat Kohli came up against a team where each person stepped up to do a role and collectively get their team over the line. The whole is greater than the sum of its parts, and the sum total of Rajasthan’s youthful exuberance coupled with their experienced campaigners ensure tha they fight on at Chepauk against SRH on Friday.
